description:
I could not find it this bug has already been reported, but I noticed some weird behaviour when using Arithmetic expressions in a SPARQL query. Specifically with respect to the -. Where the minus Symbol is used in conjunction with a multiplication symbol, the results are not shown.
The following minimal working example returned no results for ?p where I was expecting results for ?p.  Weirdly, if one of the two - is changed into a +, it will return a result for ?p.
SELECT ?s ((((?s) - 1.65) * (( ?s) - 1.65))  AS ?p) WHERE {
  VALUES(?s){
    (1.1)
    (2.2)
  }
}
Testing it on multiple different SPARQL endpoints did not result in different results:

https://api.triplydb.com/datasets/wikimedia/dbpedia/services/dbpedia/sparql version 7.2.6
http://linkeddata.finki.ukim.mk/sparql Virtuoso version 07.20.3232
http://lod.openlinksw.com/sparql Virtuoso version 07.20.3217

Workaround:
For Now I've rewritten the query to explicitly cast it to xsd:decimal. Then the query does return a result for ?p
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
SELECT ?s ((xsd:decimal((?s) - 1.65) * xsd:decimal(( ?s) - 1.65))  AS ?p)
WHERE {
  VALUES(?s){
    (1.1)
    (2.2)
  }
}
